Key Match Events: Netherlands bowler Paul van Meekeren took 4 wickets for 23 runs
Bangladesh batters struggled with the extra bounce and scored only 142 runs
Miscellaneous Highlights: The result meant the Netherlands, an associate ICC member, now sit above defending champions England and Bangladesh in the point table
Others: Dutch all-rounder Bas de Leede made an outstanding comeback by sending back two Bangladesh batters and running out Mahedi Hasan
Earlier, Netherlands skipper Scott Edwards overcame an edgy start to score a second World Cup fifty and take them to a modest 229 all out
